@startuml 04d_SequenceDiagram_EnterTestResult
title Sequence 4.4 — Enter Test Result (Field / Lab)
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left
skinparam SequenceArrowThickness 1
skinparam SequenceBoxBorderColor #000000
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #000000
skinparam SequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam SequenceParticipantBorderColor #000000
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam FontName Arial
skinparam FontSize 10
skinparam SequenceGroupBorderColor #555555
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F5F5F5

' ── Lifelines (7) — plan: KTV, EnterResultUC, ResultValidator,
'    TestingService, TestResultRepository, SqlHelper, DB (Triggers)
actor       "Field / Lab Technician"  as KTV
participant ":EnterResultUC"          as UC          <<boundary>>
participant ":ResultValidator"        as Validator   <<control>>
participant ":TestingService"         as TestService <<control>>
participant ":TestResultRepository"   as ResultRepo  <<entity>>
participant ":SqlHelper"              as SqlHelper   <<entity>>
participant "DB Triggers"             as DB          <<entity>>

note over UC, DB
  LabResultUC uses the identical flow — only the boundary form class differs.
  TestingService.EnterTestResultAsync() is shared by both EnterResultUC and LabResultUC.
end note

' ── Step 1: Technician selects sample and enters result ──────────
KTV -> UC : Select sample (sampleId, paramId), enter ResultValue,\nclick "Save"
activate UC

' ── Step 2: Client-side FluentValidation ─────────────────────────
UC -> Validator : Validate(testResultDTO)
activate Validator
note right of Validator
  AbstractValidator<TestResultDTO>
  Rules:
    ResultValue >= 0
    ParamID: NotEmpty
    TesterID: NotEmpty
    SampleID: NotEmpty
end note
Validator --> UC : return ValidationResult (IsValid, Errors)
deactivate Validator

alt [ValidationResult.IsValid = false]
    UC -> UC : Display validation error messages
    note right of UC
      User must correct input before retrying.
      Errors shown per field on the DataGridView.
    end note
end

' ── Step 3: Persist result via TestingService ────────────────────
UC -> TestService : EnterTestResultAsync(testResultDTO, reason?)
activate TestService
note right of TestService
  reason?: optional edit reason string
  (null on first entry, non-null on amendment)
end note

  TestService -> ResultRepo : SaveTestResultAsync(\nresultId, sampleId, paramId,\nresultValue, testerId)
  activate ResultRepo

    ResultRepo -> SqlHelper : ExecuteNonQueryAsync(\n"sp_SaveTestResult",\n{resultId, sampleId, paramId,\nresultValue, testerId})
    activate SqlHelper

    SqlHelper -> DB : EXEC sp_SaveTestResult\n(INSERT or UPDATE TestResults)
    activate DB

    ' ── DB Triggers fire automatically after INSERT/UPDATE ──────
    DB -> DB : TRIGGER trg_TestResults_AutoWarning\n  AFTER INSERT, UPDATE ON TestResults\n  fn_IsResultExceedingLimit(paramId, resultValue)\n  -> UPDATE TestResults SET IsWarning = 1\n     WHERE ResultValue > RegulationLimits.MaxValue
    note right of DB
      fn_IsResultExceedingLimit(paramId, value):
        SELECT MaxValue FROM RegulationLimits
        WHERE ParamID = @paramId
        RETURNS 1 if value > MaxValue, else 0
      Applies QCVN threshold check automatically.
    end note

    DB -> DB : TRIGGER trg_TestResults_AuditHistory\n  AFTER UPDATE ON TestResults\n  INSERT INTO ResultHistory\n  (HistoryID, ResultID, OldValue, NewValue,\n   ChangedBy, ChangedAt)
    note right of DB
      Captures full edit history.
      OldValue from DELETED virtual table.
      NewValue from INSERTED virtual table.
      ChangedBy = testerId from UPDATE statement.
    end note

    DB --> SqlHelper : return (rows affected = 1)
    deactivate DB

    SqlHelper --> ResultRepo : return (void)
    deactivate SqlHelper

  ResultRepo --> TestService : return TestResultDTO\n(with IsWarning flag set by trigger)
  deactivate ResultRepo

TestService --> UC : return TestResultDTO
deactivate TestService

' ── Step 4: Refresh UI ────────────────────────────────────────────
UC -> UC : Refresh DataGridView row:\n  - Highlight row in red if IsWarning = true\n  - Show warning icon in IsWarning column

deactivate UC

@enduml
